+#### 3.1.1 Making the exp-2 host trio exec-mode-aware
+
+Per Decision 1, the existing exec-mode overlays only patch the exp-1 trio, so the exp-2 trio needs its own exec-mode handling. Two shapes, in preference order:
+
+- **Preferred — env-driven entrypoint wrapper on the `-2` trio (a #147 coordination item, §11).** #147 already introduces entrypoint wrappers for the orchestrator/web-ui to gate flags on env. Extend the same mechanism to the `-2` host trio: each `*-host-2` service invokes a wrapper that reads `EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2` (defaulting to match exp-1's mode) and assembles the host CLI with `--mode subprocess` / the DooD flags / scripted as appropriate. Then a matrix cell selects the exp-2 exec mode purely through `setup-experiment` (which stamps `EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2`), and **no extra overlay file is needed**. This keeps overlay-file count flat and is symmetric with how #147 already env-gates the orchestrator. Requires #147 to land the `-2` trio wrapper-driven (or #183 to add it in wave 1).
+- **Fallback — thin `-2`-trio exec-mode overlays shipped by #183.** If the `-2` trio lands scripted-only and wrapper-retrofitting is undesirable, #183 ships `compose.multi-experiment.subprocess.yaml` (patches the three `*-host-2` `command:` blocks to subprocess mode) and `compose.multi-experiment.docker.yaml` (adds the DooD socket mount + `group_add` + `--mode docker` to the `-2` trio). Cells then layer e.g. `-f compose.yaml -f compose.subprocess.yaml -f compose.multi-experiment.yaml -f compose.multi-experiment.subprocess.yaml`. More overlay files, but clean layering and no #147 change beyond the base `-2` trio.
+
+The wrapper examples in §3.2 / §3.3 assume the **preferred** env-driven shape (exec mode selected via `setup-experiment`, `OVERLAYS` carries only the base + exp-1 exec-mode overlay + multi-experiment overlay). Under the fallback shape, each cell's `OVERLAYS` array gains the corresponding `-2`-trio overlay. The choice is the first thing wave 1 settles with #147 (§11).
